00:53:00.675 --> 00:53:02.940
and how generally
it seems like it's

00:53:02.940 --> 00:53:04.740
targeted at a
higher-end audience

00:53:04.740 --> 00:53:07.220
and has been fairly successful.

00:53:07.220 --> 00:53:11.000
And kind of how your
restaurant sits in that space.

00:53:11.000 --> 00:53:13.470
MEDWIN PANG: Everybody
looking at me?

00:53:13.470 --> 00:53:15.600
[LAUGHTER]

00:53:15.600 --> 00:53:18.080
Yeah, well, the
whole fusion movement

00:53:18.080 --> 00:53:21.150
was great, because if
it weren't for that,

00:53:21.150 --> 00:53:24.870
then every Asian restaurant,
or any other fusion restaurant,

00:53:24.870 --> 00:53:29.930
would just be whatever
the region that it's from.

00:53:29.930 --> 00:53:31.590
Right, being that
it's fusion, it

00:53:31.590 --> 00:53:37.980
makes it more
approachable to anybody.

00:53:37.980 --> 00:53:43.410
So if they add flavors that
are familiar to the locals,

00:53:43.410 --> 00:53:46.290
then they're going to
be more apt to try it.

00:53:46.290 --> 00:53:49.080
So yeah, the fusion
thing was great,

00:53:49.080 --> 00:53:51.060
though I hate the
term "fusion" myself,

00:53:51.060 --> 00:53:55.100
because that came about
for lack of better words

00:53:55.100 --> 00:53:57.390
to describe something.

00:53:57.390 --> 00:54:01.487
And it was from Nobu, where
he does Peruvian and Japanese.

00:54:01.487 --> 00:54:03.570
And it was in the review
that he was, like, oh, he

00:54:03.570 --> 00:54:04.560
does this fusion thing.

00:54:04.560 --> 00:54:07.770
So that term caught on.

00:54:07.770 --> 00:54:11.610
But yeah, it's great,
just high-end chefs

00:54:11.610 --> 00:54:14.250
from other parts of
the world, regardless

00:54:14.250 --> 00:54:16.200
of where they're from,
coming here to New York

00:54:16.200 --> 00:54:20.700
to elevate their cuisine.

00:54:20.700 --> 00:54:29.880
Anything that builds
awareness is a good thing.

00:54:29.880 --> 00:54:33.244
And without having
to cheapen yourself

00:54:33.244 --> 00:54:35.160
by saying, oh, you know,
I'm not so authentic,

00:54:35.160 --> 00:54:39.450
or I'm not so traditional,
because I add other influences,

00:54:39.450 --> 00:54:40.200
doesn't take away.

00:54:40.200 --> 00:54:43.380
It just makes it
more approachable for

00:54:43.380 --> 00:54:47.100
the average Joe to understand.

00:54:47.100 --> 00:54:52.260
EDWARD LIN: The one caveat is
to successfully fuse cuisines,

00:54:52.260 --> 00:54:55.830
you have to understand both,
or whatever you're mixing.

00:54:55.830 --> 00:54:58.980
And that's where, I
think, a lot of really--

00:54:58.980 --> 00:55:04.650
where fusion got a kind
of a bad rap, in the '90s,

00:55:04.650 --> 00:55:08.790
they were just fusing
kung pao macaroni

00:55:08.790 --> 00:55:11.850
or something like that.

00:55:11.850 --> 00:55:19.320
And if you really understand
the essence of whatever you're

00:55:19.320 --> 00:55:24.150
putting together, then you can
pick out the best parts of it

00:55:24.150 --> 00:55:30.360
and make it work on a palate
level, on a texture level,

00:55:30.360 --> 00:55:32.970
and even on a
conceptual level, where

00:55:32.970 --> 00:55:39.720
you have a history of the
dish, and it kind of gives more

00:55:39.720 --> 00:55:41.650
reason for being.

00:55:41.650 --> 00:55:45.490
I mean, Vietnamese itself
is a fusion cuisine.

00:55:45.490 --> 00:55:47.910
It's a fusion of South
Asian and French,

00:55:47.910 --> 00:55:50.365
like, naturally,
though, because--

00:55:50.365 --> 00:55:51.490
LIEN LIN: And it took time.

00:55:51.490 --> 00:55:52.531
EDWARD LIN: It took time.

00:55:52.531 --> 00:55:57.630
It took generations
of French influence

00:55:57.630 --> 00:56:00.434
and Asian influence
coming together.

00:56:00.434 --> 00:56:03.100
CHRIS CHEUNG: That's such a cool
thing though, right, to happen?

00:56:03.100 --> 00:56:04.933
EDWARD LIN: Yeah, that
is such a cool thing,

00:56:04.933 --> 00:56:05.940
when it does happen.

00:56:05.940 --> 00:56:07.398
LIEN LIN: But now
it's considered--

00:56:07.398 --> 00:56:09.970
like, banh mis are considered
a traditional Vietnamese food.

00:56:09.970 --> 00:56:10.678
EDWARD LIN: Yeah.

00:56:10.678 --> 00:56:16.030
So fusion and innovation
isn't a bad thing.

00:56:16.030 --> 00:56:21.090
It's only when it's
done wrong, when

00:56:21.090 --> 00:56:23.620
it's done thoughtlessly
and carelessly,

00:56:23.620 --> 00:56:24.956
that it becomes bad.

